        "timestamp": "2018-03-23 17:06:08.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> I need Python 2.7\n\nNo worries, we can specify that in the tox.ini.  The reason we need it is because our pypi jobs all have a tox verify step in them where they expect it.  Projects typically run tests/linters this way.  You can specify several different python versions if you wanted to.  Alternatively the tox run could be a no-op.",
